Grand Avenue, at the N.E. corner of 68th Street (left extending north), showing in four views at the corner, the home of Judge William Burcham in 1873 which was demolished in June 1925. It is said that this house is on the site of the John Firth house of 1850. One Doyle was an occupant of the house seen in these views. View No. four shows a rear of the house viewed across the B.R.T. tracks paralleling Borden Avenue.
